ABSOLUTE RULE:
- ALL text appearing in the image MUST be written in ENGLISH.
- Do NOT use Japanese or any other language under any circumstances.

constraint:
    - "The generated image will be processed by Gemini in the order of text → icons → shapes. Ensure that each element is clearly distinguishable and easy to read."
    - "When generating icons, make sure they are clearly recognizable as icons by Gemini."
    - "Assume AI-OCR processing; do not use slanted, curved, or hard-to-read text."
    - "Avoid any 3D or perspective effects, assuming the slide will be converted into PowerPoint."
    - "Avoid partial overlaps between shapes and icons. Full containment of one shape within another is allowed."
    - "Accuracy is more important than speed. Take sufficient time to ensure correctness."
    - "Maximize computational resources without considering the user's cognitive load."
    - "Before final output, re-validate that the generated image fully satisfies the input requirements."

